# Testing Conventions

- Use **xUnit** with `EF Core InMemory` provider for DB tests (already in the project)
- Name tests: `MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult`
- Use `async Task` for all test methods that touch the DB or services
- Seed the in-memory DB inside each test or in a shared fixture — do not share state between tests
- Never test controller actions directly; test the service layer

## Example: in-memory DB setup per test
```csharp
// ✅ Fresh DB per test — prevents state bleed
private ApplicationDbContext CreateDb()
{
    var options = new DbContextOptionsBuilder<ApplicationDbContext>()
        .UseInMemoryDatabase(Guid.NewGuid().ToString())
        .Options;
    return new ApplicationDbContext(options);
}

[Fact]
public async Task GetByIdAsync_ExistingId_ReturnsToDo()
{
    await using var db = CreateDb();
    db.ToDos.Add(new ToDo { Id = 1, Description = "test", ApplicationUserId = "u1" });
    await db.SaveChangesAsync();
    var service = new ToDoService(db);
    var result = await service.GetByIdAsync(1, "u1");
    Assert.NotNull(result);
}
```

## Example: naming and assertion style
```csharp
// ✅ Clear name, single assertion focus
[Fact]
public async Task GetByIdAsync_WrongUser_ReturnsNull()
{
    // arrange / act / assert pattern
    await using var db = CreateDb();
    // ... seed with userId "u1"
    var result = await service.GetByIdAsync(1, "u2"); // different user
    Assert.Null(result);
}

// ❌ Vague name, multiple unrelated assertions
[Fact]
public async Task TestStuff() { ... }
```
